Name: Documents URL
guidance: Discard. If no `ParticipationFee` object in the `tender.participationFees` array has a `.type` of 'document', then access is unrestricted.

Name: Documents Restricted URL
guidance: Add a `ParticipationFee` object to the `tender.participationFees` array, set its `.type` to 'document', and set its `.id` to '1'.

Name: Internal Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Reference number* be equal to the `ocid` value. Map to `tender.id` (string).

Name: Description
guidance: Map to the lot's `.description`\n\n**F12, F13**: Instead, map to `tender.description`

Name: Main Classification Code
guidance: Set `tender.classification.scheme` to 'CPV', take the CPV code in the `CODE` attribute, and map to `tender.classification.id`

Name: Organisation Country Subdivision
guidance: Take the NUTS code in the `CODE` attribute, and map to the party's `.address.region`\n\nThere's an open issue ([#739](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/739)) about region codes. (ISSUE)

Name: Organisation Country Code
guidance: Take the country code in the `VALUE` attribute, translate to a country name, and map to the party's `.address.countryName`\n\nThere's an open issue ([#524](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/524)) to add a `.countryCode` field to the `Address` object, to avoid translation. (ISSUE)

Name: Activity Authority
guidance: Get the `Organization` object for the buyer, and add a `Classification` object to its `.details.classifications` array. Set the classification's `.scheme` to ['COFOG'](https://unstats.un.org/unsd/publications/catalogue?selectID=145), and set its `.id` and/or `.description` as follows:

Name: Buyer Legal Type
guidance: Get the `Organization` object for the buyer, and add a `Classification` object to its `.details.classifications` array. Set the classification's `.scheme` to 'TED_CA_TYPE', and set its `.id` and/or `.description` as follows:

Name: Place Performance Country Subdivision
guidance: For each `NUTS` element, take the NUTS code in its `CODE` attribute, add an `Address` object to the item's `.deliveryAddresses` array, and map to its `.region`.\n\nThere's an open issue ([#739](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/739)) about region codes. (ISSUE)

Name: Documents URL
guidance: Discard. If no `ParticipationFee` object in the `tender.participationFees` array has a `.type` of 'document', then access is unrestricted.

Name: Documents Restricted URL
guidance: Add a `ParticipationFee` object to the `tender.participationFees` array, set its `.type` to 'document', and set its `.id` to '1'.

Name: Submission Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Submission Electronic
guidance: Add 'electronicSubmission' to `tender.submissionMethod`, and map to `tender.submissionMethodDetails`\n\nIf *to the following address* is selected, this results in a loss of structure. (WARNING #27)

Name: Submission URL
guidance: Add 'written' to `tender.submissionMethod`, and discard. Tenders or requests to participate must be submitted to the abovementioned address unless otherwised specified.

Name: Deadline Receipt Expressions
guidance: Map to the date component of `tender.tenderPeriod.endDate`

Name: Submission Language
guidance: Lowercase and add to the `tender.submissionTerms.languages` array

Name: Purpose Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Internal Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Reference number* be equal to the `ocid` value. Map to `tender.id` (string).

Name: Main Classification Code
guidance: Set `tender.classification.scheme` to 'CPV', take the CPV code in the `CODE` attribute, and map to `tender.classification.id`

Name: Group Framework Estimated Maximum Value Lot Identifier
Duration Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Procedure Type
guidance: Set `tender.procurementMethod` to 'selective', and set `tender.procurementMethodDetails` to 'Restricted procedure'

Name: Lots All Required
guidance: Set `tender.lotDetails.maximumLotsBidPerSupplier` to the number (not the string) 1e9999 (which parses to infinity i.e. "all")

Name: Funds Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: EU Funds
guidance:
* Get the `Organization` object whose `.name` is 'European Union'. If none exists yet:
  * [Add a party](../../operations/#add-a-party)
  * Set its `.name` to 'European Union'
* Add 'funder' to its `.roles`

* Get the `Finance` object whose `.description` is the *Identification of the project*. If none exists yet:
  * Add a `Finance` object to the `planning.budget.finance` array
  * Map the *Identification of the project* to its `.description`
  * Set its `.id` incrementally
  * Set its `.financingParty.name` to 'European Union'
  * Set its `.financingParty.id` to the party's `.id`
  * Add the lot's `.id` to its `.relatedLots` (**F12, F13**: Instead, do nothing)

In [future forms](https://github.com/eForms/eForms/issues/181#issuecomment-439861320), this field will be de-emphasized.

Name: Selection Criteria Type
guidance: Add a `SelectionCriterion` object to the `tender.selectionCriteria.criteria` array and set its `.type` to 'technical'. If *Reference to the relevant law, regulation or administrative provision* is set, map it to the criterion's `.description`. Otherwise, set the criterion's `.description` to 'Execution of the service is reserved to a particular profession'.

Name: Selection Criteria Name
guidance: Add a `SelectionCriterion` object to the `tender.selectionCriteria.criteria` array, set its `.type` to 'economic', and map to its `.description`.

Name: Selection Criteria Description
guidance: Get the `SelectionCriterion` object whose `.type` is 'economic', and map to its `.minimum`

* Get the `Organization` object whose `.name` is 'European Union'. If none exists yet:
  * [Add a party](../../operations/#add-a-party)
  * Set its `.name` to 'European Union'
* Add 'funder' to its `.roles`

* Get the `Finance` object whose `.description` is the *Identification of the project*. If none exists yet:
  * Add a `Finance` object to the `planning.budget.finance` array
  * Map the *Identification of the project* to its `.description`
  * Set its `.id` incrementally
  * Set its `.financingParty.name` to 'European Union'
  * Set its `.financingParty.id` to the party's `.id`
  * Add the lot's `.id` to its `.relatedLots` (**F12, F13**: Instead, do nothing)

In [future forms](https://github.com/eForms/eForms/issues/181#issuecomment-439861320), this field will be de-emphasized.

Name: Selection Criteria Type
guidance: Add a `SelectionCriterion` object to the `tender.selectionCriteria.criteria` array and set its `.type` to 'technical'. If *Reference to the relevant law, regulation or administrative provision* is set, map it to the criterion's `.description`. Otherwise, set the criterion's `.description` to 'Execution of the service is reserved to a particular profession'.

Name: Selection Criteria Name
guidance: Add a `SelectionCriterion` object to the `tender.selectionCriteria.criteria` array, set its `.type` to 'economic', and map to its `.description`.

Name: Selection Criteria Description
guidance: Get the `SelectionCriterion` object whose `.type` is 'economic', and map to its `.minimum`

Name: Selection Criteria Second Stage Invite Number
Selection Criteria Second Stage Invite Number Weight
Selection Criteria Second Stage Invite Number Threshold
Organisation Country Subdivision
guidance: Take the NUTS code in the `CODE` attribute, and map to the party's `.address.region`\n\nThere's an open issue ([#739](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/739)) about region codes. (ISSUE)

Name: Organisation Country Code
guidance: Take the country code in the `VALUE` attribute, translate to a country name, and map to the party's `.address.countryName`\n\nThere's an open issue ([#524](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/524)) to add a `.countryCode` field to the `Address` object, to avoid translation. (ISSUE)

Name: Activity Authority
guidance: Get the `Organization` object for the buyer, and add a `Classification` object to its `.details.classifications` array. Set the classification's `.scheme` to ['COFOG'](https://unstats.un.org/unsd/publications/catalogue?selectID=145), and set its `.id` and/or `.description` as follows:

Name: Buyer Legal Type
guidance: Get the `Organization` object for the buyer, and add a `Classification` object to its `.details.classifications` array. Set the classification's `.scheme` to 'TED_CA_TYPE', and set its `.id` and/or `.description` as follows:

Name: Award Criteria Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Place Performance Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Place Performance Country Subdivision
guidance: For each `NUTS` element, take the NUTS code in its `CODE` attribute, add an `Address` object to the item's `.deliveryAddresses` array, and map to its `.region`.\n\nThere's an open issue ([#739](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/739)) about region codes. (ISSUE)

Name: Additional Information Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Additional Information
guidance: Append to the lot's `.description`\n\nThis results in a loss of structure. (WARNING #28)

Name: Dispatch Invitation Tender
guidance: Map to the time component of `tender.tenderPeriod.endDate`

Name: Documents URL
guidance: Discard. If no `ParticipationFee` object in the `tender.participationFees` array has a `.type` of 'document', then access is unrestricted.

Name: Documents Restricted URL
guidance: Add a `ParticipationFee` object to the `tender.participationFees` array, set its `.type` to 'document', and set its `.id` to '1'.

Name: Deadline Receipt Tenders
guidance: Map to the date component of `tender.tenderPeriod.endDate`

Name: Deadline Receipt Requests
guidance: Map to the date component of `tender.tenderPeriod.endDate`

Name: Public Opening Date
guidance: Map to the date component of `tender.awardPeriod.startDate` and to the date component of `tender.bidOpening.date`

Name: Submission Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Submission Electronic
guidance: Add 'electronicSubmission' to `tender.submissionMethod`, and map to `tender.submissionMethodDetails`\n\nIf *to the following address* is selected, this results in a loss of structure. (WARNING #27)

Name: Submission URL
guidance: Add 'written' to `tender.submissionMethod`, and discard. Tenders or requests to participate must be submitted to the abovementioned address unless otherwised specified.

Name: Submission Language
guidance: Lowercase and add to the `tender.submissionTerms.languages` array

Name: Purpose Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Internal Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Reference number* be equal to the `ocid` value. Map to `tender.id` (string).

Name: Main Classification Code
guidance: Set `tender.classification.scheme` to 'CPV', take the CPV code in the `CODE` attribute, and map to `tender.classification.id`

Name: Group Framework Estimated Maximum Value Lot Identifier
Duration Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Lots All Required
guidance: Set `tender.lotDetails.maximumLotsBidPerSupplier` to the number (not the string) 1e9999 (which parses to infinity i.e. "all")

Name: Second Stage Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Funds Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Purpose Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Internal Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Reference number* be equal to the `ocid` value. Map to `tender.id` (string).

Name: Main Classification Code
guidance: Set `tender.classification.scheme` to 'CPV', take the CPV code in the `CODE` attribute, and map to `tender.classification.id`

Name: Group Framework Estimated Maximum Value Lot Identifier
Duration Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Funds Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: EU Funds
guidance:
* Get the `Organization` object whose `.name` is 'European Union'. If none exists yet:
  * [Add a party](../../operations/#add-a-party)
  * Set its `.name` to 'European Union'
* Add 'funder' to its `.roles`

* Get the `Finance` object whose `.description` is the *Identification of the project*. If none exists yet:
  * Add a `Finance` object to the `planning.budget.finance` array
  * Map the *Identification of the project* to its `.description`
  * Set its `.id` incrementally
  * Set its `.financingParty.name` to 'European Union'
  * Set its `.financingParty.id` to the party's `.id`
  * Add the lot's `.id` to its `.relatedLots` (**F12, F13**: Instead, do nothing)

In [future forms](https://github.com/eForms/eForms/issues/181#issuecomment-439861320), this field will be de-emphasized.

Name: Selection Criteria Type
guidance: Add a `SelectionCriterion` object to the `tender.selectionCriteria.criteria` array and set its `.type` to 'technical'. If *Reference to the relevant law, regulation or administrative provision* is set, map it to the criterion's `.description`. Otherwise, set the criterion's `.description` to 'Execution of the service is reserved to a particular profession'.

Name: Selection Criteria Second Stage Invite Number
Selection Criteria Second Stage Invite Number Weight
Selection Criteria Second Stage Invite Number Threshold
Organisation Country Subdivision
guidance: Take the NUTS code in the `CODE` attribute, and map to the party's `.address.region`\n\nThere's an open issue ([#739](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/739)) about region codes. (ISSUE)

Name: Organisation Country Code
guidance: Take the country code in the `VALUE` attribute, translate to a country name, and map to the party's `.address.countryName`\n\nThere's an open issue ([#524](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/524)) to add a `.countryCode` field to the `Address` object, to avoid translation. (ISSUE)

Name: Activity Authority
guidance: Get the `Organization` object for the buyer, and add a `Classification` object to its `.details.classifications` array. Set the classification's `.scheme` to ['COFOG'](https://unstats.un.org/unsd/publications/catalogue?selectID=145), and set its `.id` and/or `.description` as follows:

Name: Place Performance Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Place Performance Country Subdivision
guidance: For each `NUTS` element, take the NUTS code in its `CODE` attribute, add an `Address` object to the item's `.deliveryAddresses` array, and map to its `.region`.\n\nThere's an open issue ([#739](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/739)) about region codes. (ISSUE)

Name: Additional Information Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Additional Information
guidance: Append to the lot's `.description`\n\nThis results in a loss of structure. (WARNING #28)

Name: Dispatch Invitation Tender
guidance: Lowercase and add to the `tender.submissionTerms.languages` array

Name: Deadline Receipt Requests
guidance: Map to the time component of `tender.tenderPeriod.endDate`

Name: Guarantee Required Description
guidance: Add a `SelectionCriterion` object to the `tender.selectionCriteria.criteria` array, set its `.type` to 'suitability', and map to its `.description`.

Name: Main Nature
guidance: For each `CODE` attribute, add a `Classification` object to the `tender.additionalClassifications` array, set its `.scheme` to 'CPVS', prefix by the *Main CPV code*, and map to its `.id`. Remove any duplicate entries from the `tender.additionalClassifications` array.

Name: Group Framework Estimated Maximum Value Lot Identifier
Selection Criteria Second Stage Invite Number
Selection Criteria Second Stage Invite Number Weight
Selection Criteria Second Stage Invite Number Threshold
Organisation Country Code
guidance: Take the country code in the `VALUE` attribute, translate to a country name, and map to the party's `.address.countryName`\n\nThere's an open issue ([#524](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/524)) to add a `.countryCode` field to the `Address` object, to avoid translation. (ISSUE)

Name: Place Performance Additional Information
guidance: For each `CODE` attribute, add a `Classification` object to the `tender.additionalClassifications` array, set its `.scheme` to 'CPVS', prefix by the *Main CPV code*, and map to its `.id`. Remove any duplicate entries from the `tender.additionalClassifications` array.

guidance: Map to the time component of `tender.tenderPeriod.endDate`

Name: Documents Restricted
guidance: Add a `ParticipationFee` object to the `tender.participationFees` array, set its `.type` to 'document', and set its `.id` to '1'.

Name: Documents URL
guidance: Discard. If no `ParticipationFee` object in the `tender.participationFees` array has a `.type` of 'document', then access is unrestricted.

Name: Deadline Receipt Tenders
guidance: Map to the date component of `tender.tenderPeriod.endDate`

guidance: Map to the date component of `tender.tenderPeriod.endDate`

guidance: Add 'electronicSubmission' to `tender.submissionMethod`, and map to `tender.submissionMethodDetails`\n\nIf *to the following address* is selected, this results in a loss of structure. (WARNING #27)

Name: Submission URL
guidance: Add 'written' to `tender.submissionMethod`, and discard. Tenders or requests to participate must be submitted to the abovementioned address unless otherwised specified.

guidance: Discard. If no `ParticipationFee` object in the `tender.participationFees` array has a `.type` of 'document', then access is unrestricted.

Name: Documents Restricted URL
guidance: Add a `ParticipationFee` object to the `tender.participationFees` array, set its `.type` to 'document', and set its `.id` to '1'.

Name: Purpose Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Internal Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Reference number* be equal to the `ocid` value. Map to `tender.id` (string).

Name: Description
guidance: Map to the lot's `.description`\n\n**F12, F13**: Instead, map to `tender.description`

Name: Main Classification Code
guidance: Set `tender.classification.scheme` to 'CPV', take the CPV code in the `CODE` attribute, and map to `tender.classification.id`

Name: Group Framework Estimated Maximum Value Lot Identifier
Organisation Country Subdivision
guidance: Take the NUTS code in the `CODE` attribute, and map to the party's `.address.region`\n\nThere's an open issue ([#739](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/739)) about region codes. (ISSUE)

Name: Organisation Country Code
guidance: Take the country code in the `VALUE` attribute, translate to a country name, and map to the party's `.address.countryName`\n\nThere's an open issue ([#524](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/524)) to add a `.countryCode` field to the `Address` object, to avoid translation. (ISSUE)

Name: Activity Authority
guidance: Get the `Organization` object for the buyer, and add a `Classification` object to its `.details.classifications` array. Set the classification's `.scheme` to ['COFOG'](https://unstats.un.org/unsd/publications/catalogue?selectID=145), and set its `.id` and/or `.description` as follows:

Name: Buyer Legal Type
guidance: Get the `Organization` object for the buyer, and add a `Classification` object to its `.details.classifications` array. Set the classification's `.scheme` to 'TED_CA_TYPE', and set its `.id` and/or `.description` as follows:

Name: Place Performance Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Place Performance Country Subdivision
guidance: For each `NUTS` element, take the NUTS code in its `CODE` attribute, add an `Address` object to the item's `.deliveryAddresses` array, and map to its `.region`.\n\nThere's an open issue ([#739](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/739)) about region codes. (ISSUE)

Name: Additional Information Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: Internal Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Reference number* be equal to the `ocid` value. Map to `tender.id` (string).

Name: Main Classification Code
guidance: Copy the `Item` object in `tender.items` to `.items` on the `Contract` object in `contracts`, and delete the contract's item's `.classification` and `.additionalClassifications`.

Name: Funds Lot Identifier
guidance: If not set, let *Lot No* be '1'. Map to the lot's `.id` (string), map to the item's `.id` (string), and map to the item's `.relatedLot` (string).

Name: EU Funds
guidance:
* Get the `Organization` object whose `.name` is 'European Union'. If none exists yet:
  * [Add a party](../../operations/#add-a-party)
  * Set its `.name` to 'European Union'
* Add 'funder' to its `.roles`

* Get the `Finance` object whose `.description` is the *Identification of the project*. If none exists yet:
  * Add a `Finance` object to the `planning.budget.finance` array
  * Map the *Identification of the project* to its `.description`
  * Set its `.id` incrementally
  * Set its `.financingParty.name` to 'European Union'
  * Set its `.financingParty.id` to the party's `.id`
  * Add the lot's `.id` to its `.relatedLots` (**F12, F13**: Instead, do nothing)

In [future forms](https://github.com/eForms/eForms/issues/181#issuecomment-439861320), this field will be de-emphasized.
